China reiterated its "one country, two systems" approach to Taiwan while introducing an anti-secession law.
The Mainland Affairs Council closely monitors China's communication with the US regarding this law.
President Chen Shui-bian warned that Beijing's proposed law could destabilize the region.
Taiwan expressed opposition to the legislation, fearing it could lead to arrests of Taiwanese visitors to the mainland.
The US and EU also criticized China's plan, urging for peaceful resolutions.
Taiwan plans to counteract the law through legislative measures and a referendum.
The Legislative Yuan will pass a resolution opposing Beijing's anti-secession legislation.
